Political Capital: Hungarian Guard has increased country risk
According to the Risk Analysis Division of Political Capital (Risk Analyzing Division), the activity of the Hungarian Guard, formed last August with the support of Jobbik Magyarorsz<0xC3><0xA1>gért Mozgalom (Movement for a Better Hungary), increases the political risk of Hungary and the region in several aspects.
In its “risk warning”, the company points out that, in relation to the activity of the Hungarian Guard, the greatest political risk is already that “in the short term aggressive ethnic clashes can occur following the aggravation of the already existing ethnic tension between the Gypsy and non-Gypsy populations of Hungary”.
The research institute added that the Hungarian Guard's political strategy likely to provoke this situation is the main reason.
As they say, this is explained by one of the main shortcomings of Hungarian political actors: "public actors passed the public debate on the Roma case to representatives of radical and extreme political groups who based a political strategy on the dispute between Gypsies and Hungarians".
