Congress approves the transposition of Mifid, which came into force on November 1
Alongside its parliamentary formality, which ended today with the vote of the Congress on the amendments incorporated into the draft in the Senate, the Government submitted to a public hearing the regulations that will develop the new law, with the objective of its entry into force before the end of the year.
The representatives of the various groups agreed to highlight the efforts made by Members of Parliament and Senators to negotiate and agree on the best possible regulation to ensure investor protection and to regulate in detail the activities of the agencies so that the markets function effectively.
MIFID, which amends the Securities Markets Act, involves the modernisation of financial markets, as it strengthens investor protection, enhances the powers of the leaders of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and promotes cooperation between the different leaders of the European Union.
The new regulation will provide financial advisory services for specialized social reasons as well as for natural or legal persons and will create a new type of financial services (ESIS), financial advisory companies (FIAs), which merge with securities companies, securities agencies and portfolio management companies.
In addition, it increases the number of systems for the execution of transactions on financial instruments, so that it is possible to add to regulated secondary markets multilateral trading systems and order internationalization systems, which face competition from current exchange managers.
The Act also requires investment services companies to disclose information on key aspects of their business profile, exposure to risk and forms of risk management on the market, and it requires them to keep a record of all transactions they carry out, to facilitate control by CNMV.
Passing through the Congressional Economics Commission, several amendments have been added, one of which highlights that the securitized debts will be considered a "complex" financial instrument given its high risk to the investor, which has been demonstrated with what happened to the US high-risk mortgage debt (subprime).
In addition, they took advantage of the management's transposition benefited to legally delimit the functions that graduates in Economics can have 30 years after in 1977, was approved, the Royal Decree which delimits the professional functions reserved for economists.
For its part, the Senate has incorporated the creation of new figures in the financial sector, such as that of the mediator, who will work on behalf of a company, who will not require the authorization of the CNMV and who will be able to lend its services of marketing products and attracting new customers to different investment companies at the same time.
