What insurance is appropriate for me?
Automobile insurance, which covers the driver in the face of possible accidents, involves a significant expense that will depend on various factors, such as age, sex, the seniority of the driver's license, the marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use made of it, among others.
Having a car is the main thing.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing the vehicle model.
And it is that, choosing the right car insurance, is even more difficult than choosing the model of the vehicle.
Car insurance is an agreement between an insurance company and the insurer.
This compromise is embodied in an insurance contract, which establishes that the company receives the value of the premium granted and in return it becomes liable for the obligation to pay compensation in the event of a claim.
The premium is the price of the insurance, which is established taking into account various factors, such as age, sex, the seniority of the driver's license, the marital status, the type of vehicle to be insured or the use made of it, among others.
Insurance companies determine their prices based on statistics, so that the higher the probability of an accident, the higher the rating to be paid.
This is why people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower premiums, since statistics show that these people have a lower casualty rate than their caution.
Similarly, using censuses, the companies concluded that married people tend to have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The use of the vehicle will affect the frequency, and therefore the likelihood of an accident.
By increasing the frequency, the odds increase.
There are many variables that insurers take into account when determining the premium price.
This is why the driver must carefully study the situation in order to choose the car insurance that best suits his profile.
Here we will expose the most significant variables when choosing one or the other type of insurance, so that it, in addition to adapting to the characteristics of the insurer, offers him a reasonable price.
Young people under the age of 25 face a variety of disadvantages when entering into an insurance contract at an affordable price, such as low driving experience and seniority of the driver's license.
Although the ideal to be well-insured is an all-risk insurance, other more economical options exist.
The most forward-thinking drivers can opt for any risk insurance with deductible, so that they get insurance coverage at any risk but at a more affordable price.
This form of agreement implies that the customer pays a part of the amount of the claim.
"The portion of the amount of the claim that the customer pays will be determined based on the value of the premium, which will be higher the amount will be low," Luis Noguera, the head in Spain of First Europa, an online insurance broker, specifies.
Another option is extended third party insurance, so that the customer provides protection to deal with damage caused to third parties, but by those caused on his own car.
In addition, it would be covered against theft, fires and loss of the vehicle.
A piece of advice.
If you are under the age of 25, try to be careful and avoid claims as much as possible, as this will affect the bonus, which can reduce the price of insurance in the future.
A bonus is a reduction in the basic rate that the company has.
On the contrary, a penalty is an increase in the basic rate.
“The bonuses and sanctions will depend on the company and its profit.
If the company has had a good year it can afford to increase the bonuses," clarifies Noguera.
Beyond the age of 25, it becomes easier for drivers to enter into an insurance contract, as the rate of damages is reduced thanks to the accumulated experience.
It is for this reason that it is better to choose an all-risk insurance with deductible.
"Normally young people cannot benefit from the experience gained in advance after an accident," says the director of the European company in Spain and adds that the majority of accidents occur during the second year of driving, once the 'novice fear' has passed.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is better that he negotiates insurance at all risk, as long as his economic situation allows it.
Marriages with children are considered by insurers to be the people with the lowest loss rate, because the increases will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be an all-risk insurance with deductible (may be 300 euros), or a third-party insurance extended from the third year of life of the vehicle when the insured has a high level of bonus.
“They have a more casual drive and they have a greater purchasing power to afford the luxury of assuming a larger amount of franchises,” said Luis Noguera.
For pensioners, an all-risk insurance with deductible is preferable (being the one of 150 euros), or an extended third-party insurance when the insurer has a high level of bonus.
It must be said that car insurance is something important, not only because it covers the driver in the face of possible accidents, but also because it represents a significant expense, it is for this reason that it is fundamental to properly study the insurance that suits us most according to our personal situation.
