The supergroups of Germany of the seventies are playing again: the three members of the group Harmonia again took their console in a concert in Berlin.
For their return, recordings of their great success "Live 1974" were released.
Already at that time, they were much more known abroad.
The expected sensation then occurs in the form of three gentlemen announced at the evening poster.
Everyone has their little box in front of them, their cable and, above all, their buttons.
Dieter Moebius, 63, sits in the middle in a snow-white shirt.
He is flanked to the left by Michael Rother, a 57-year-old with a laptop and guitar.
To the right, observed by the whole auditorium, Hans-Joachim Roedelius, 73, bends over his console.
